1
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:13,933
<i>You're actually pointing
your finger at your mother?</i>

2
00:00:14,067 --> 00:00:17,500
<i>And if the man you're talking
about was beaten,</i>

3
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:19,367
<i> he's probably a bad person.</i>

4
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,167
<i> Have you ever thought of that?</i>

5
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:24,600
<i>And you, Robles, make sure
no witnesses will come out.</i>

6
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,900
<i>Or else, I'll follow you
to Dante.</i>

7
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:28,067
<i> Don't worry, Boss.</i>

8
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,400
<i>I'll clean up all the mess
Dante left behind.</i>

9
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:33,700
<i>What's the news about
Dante Eusebio's relatives?</i>

10
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,533
<i>- Have they spoken to them?
- They didn't come.</i>

11
00:00:35,667 --> 00:00:37,100
<i> In case you need my help...</i>

12
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:38,967
<i> to speak to him, let me know.</i>

13
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,033
<i> Okay, Chief.</i>

14
00:00:40,167 --> 00:00:41,467
<i>I'll study this case
at my house.</i>

15
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,500
<i> You can't go home.</i>

16
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:43,567
<i> Stay here at the station.</i>

17
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:44,900
<i> Did I hear that right, Chief?</i>

18
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:46,033
<i> I'm not allowed to go home?</i>

19
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,167
<i> Robles' house is really big...</i>

20
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:50,200
<i> for a police officer's salary.</i>

21
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:52,100
<i> It's not money that I'm after.</i>

22
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:55,567
<i>My only request is that I hope
you don't have to file charges.</i>

23
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,667
<i>My grandmother
is more important to me.</i>

24
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:58,667
<i> Don't worry about it.</i>

25
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,367
<i> We'll drop the case.</i>

26
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:01,633
<i> What's the news?</i>

27
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:03,100
<i> The house is big.</i>

28
00:01:03,233 --> 00:01:05,433
<i>It looks like he made a lot of
money from the syndicates.</i>

29
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:06,567
<i>- It's open.
- Chief...</i>

30
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:07,800
<i> Hurry up!</i>

31
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:09,833
<i>You know, Robles wanted
to go home from the start.</i>

32
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:12,733
<i>So if I stop him again,
he might notice something.</i>

33
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:16,000
<i>What are you doing
in Robles' house, Conde?</i>

34
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:22,167
Sir, here are the files
you asked for.

35
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:23,767
Thank you, Noble.

36
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,233
Bok.

37
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:30,467
Bok, by the way, where did
Tonyo and Garcia go?

38
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,733
They left earlier.

39
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:35,900
I heard that the witness

40
00:01:36,033 --> 00:01:38,167
who is Dante Eusebio's relative
stood them up.

41
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:39,767
I don't know about that.

42
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:41,633
Why?

43
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,733
No, I was going to offer to
convince the witness.

44
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,033
Come on, Bok,
don't make an offer.

45
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:48,833
We have a lot of work here.

46
00:01:48,967 --> 00:01:50,867
We need to finish this.

47
00:02:06,433 --> 00:02:08,800
Bok, let me just answer this.

48
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:10,033
Hey, come back.

49
00:02:10,167 --> 00:02:11,100
There's a lot more.

50
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:12,900
Yes, I'll be back.

51
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:23,267
Hello? What do you need?

52
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,533
You're so thick-faced,
aren't you?

53
00:02:25,667 --> 00:02:28,300
You're meeting Conde
at your house.

54
00:02:28,433 --> 00:02:30,667
What? Are you betraying us?

55
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,067
What are you talking about?
I'm at the station.

56
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,800
So what is Conde doing here
at your house?

57
00:02:35,933 --> 00:02:37,200
What?

58
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:38,900
Wait, wait, wait...

59
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:40,533
If you're at the station,

60
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:42,467
and Conde and his partner are
here at your house...

61
00:02:43,767 --> 00:02:46,100
That means they're
investigating me.

62
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:17,900
You undermined me in front of
that bastard!

63
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:19,867
You're really like your father!

64
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,467
I am not my father.

65
00:03:23,167 --> 00:03:24,633
Mom, listen to me.

66
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:26,333
Look at the optics.

67
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:30,667
Am I going to let my mother
oppress my illegitimate sister?

68
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:34,300
What will the people
of Calabari say to me?

69
00:03:34,433 --> 00:03:37,733
Do you think they'll vote for me
in the next election?

70
00:03:37,867 --> 00:03:39,667
So it was just a political move?

71
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,067
Of course!

72
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,000
You don't like Bobby either?

73
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,367
All along...

74
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:50,033
I thought I was
dad's first born.

75
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,833
I thought I was the eldest.

76
00:03:51,967 --> 00:03:53,833
I wasn't. It was all a lie.

77
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,467
Bobby came first,

78
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,500
and that makes me feel used.

79
00:03:57,633 --> 00:03:59,700
Thank God!

80
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:03,067
I thought you weren't using
your brains anymore!

81
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:07,133
I thought I didn't have any
allies in the family anymore.

82
00:04:07,267 --> 00:04:10,533
I thought Bobby had taken
you away from me,

83
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,267
you and Faye.

84
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:19,767
I'm just being nice to her
because my position requires it.

85
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:22,567
But she's not
part of our family.

86
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,033
She never was.

87
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:26,067
She never will be.

88
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,767
Leave the station right now.

89
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,767
- Bok, I have to go home.
- Hey, wait a minute.

90
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:52,367
Didn't Chief say
no one's leaving until...

91
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,633
I said there's an emergency!

92
00:04:54,767 --> 00:04:55,833
Robles!

93
00:04:55,967 --> 00:04:57,567
Where are you going?

94
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:59,267
Didn't I tell you not to leave?

95
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,767
Chief, we have
a family emergency.

96
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,367
I have to go home.

97
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:03,967
Don't you dare leave!

98
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:25,333
What are you doing?

99
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:26,833
Get out!

100
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:28,467
I said, get out!

101
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:34,367
Get out!

102
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:37,700
Get out.

103
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:45,600
Robles is something else,
isn't he?

104
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:47,233
He's good at covering
his tracks.

105
00:05:47,367 --> 00:05:49,767
We didn't find any evidence
other than the passbook.

106
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:53,333
Oh, what's that?

107
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:56,733
That red car,

108
00:05:56,867 --> 00:05:57,967
I noticed it earlier.

109
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,033
It arrived at the same time
as us.

110
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:02,133
It's still there.

111
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,333
What are you guys up to?

112
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:13,600
Sorry,

113
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:18,567
but let's see who'll go first.

114
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,000
Don't mind that.

115
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:32,267
Let's go to Station 12.

116
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:46,100
Robles, let's talk.

117
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:48,967
You, get Chief.

118
00:06:50,433 --> 00:06:52,133
I said get Chief!

119
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,533
Chief...

120
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,867
Get him in there! Quick!

121
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,933
- Mira!
- Jake...

122
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,233
what's going on here?

123
00:07:24,367 --> 00:07:27,600
It's Lieutenant Robles, he took
our colleagues hostage upstairs.

124
00:07:27,733 --> 00:07:28,400
What?

125
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:31,033
Wait a minute...

126
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:33,600
Oh, what are you doing?

127
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:35,967
Jake, I need to report this.

128
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:39,000
The people have the right to
know what's going on here.

129
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:45,367
- Noble.
- Ma'am!

130
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:46,567
What's going on?

131
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,700
Ma'am, it's Chief, Lieutenant
Robles shot him,

132
00:07:48,867 --> 00:07:51,367
and then he took Lieutenant
Dizon and Bautista as hostages.

133
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:52,367
What?

134
00:07:54,133 --> 00:07:56,633
Ma'am, what's our strategy?

135
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:58,033
Shall we go in, Ma'am?

136
00:07:58,167 --> 00:07:59,233
No.

137
00:07:59,367 --> 00:08:00,667
Secure the perimeter.

138
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,333
Yes, Ma'am.

139
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:04,133
- Let's secure the area.
- Let's secure the area!

140
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,200
It's driving me crazy!
I'm so pissed off!

141
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,233
Did Ma'am Sophia ambush you?

142
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:15,400
Never mind,

143
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:17,100
Glen already apologized.

144
00:08:17,233 --> 00:08:20,567
And we also talked properly.

145
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,233
Properly?

146
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:25,033
Oh my, for sure,

147
00:08:25,167 --> 00:08:28,300
your stepmother
is just faking it.

148
00:08:28,433 --> 00:08:30,733
I know that.

149
00:08:30,867 --> 00:08:32,600
But that's it,

150
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:34,500
I told them the only thing
that matters to me

151
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:35,567
is peace of mind.

152
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:38,767
And they shouldn't bother
grandmother anymore.

153
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,067
How are you guys doing here?

154
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,933
Well,

155
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:45,833
a live chicken almost ate us.

156
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,300
What?

157
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:50,500
Oh my girl, it's a long story.

158
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:52,300
And it seems like

159
00:08:52,433 --> 00:08:56,667
the symptoms of the Captain's
illness are getting worse.

160
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,300
Oh my...

161
00:09:00,433 --> 00:09:01,767
what do you think?

162
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:06,033
Should I continue my leave?

163
00:09:06,167 --> 00:09:08,567
What do you mean continue?

164
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:12,433
I'll go straight to resigning.

165
00:09:12,567 --> 00:09:14,200
- What?
- What?

166
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:29,533
Oh, it's Lieutenant Samson.

167
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:31,833
I knew it,
she has a crush on you.

168
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:36,800
Lieutenant Samson,
what's the news?

169
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:39,733
Tonyo, are you near the station?

170
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:41,367
A bit close.

171
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:42,500
Why?

172
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:44,033
<i> There's a big mess here!</i>

173
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:45,233
What mess?

174
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:47,333
It's Robles, he took
Major Flores hostage.

175
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:48,333
Get back here.

176
00:09:49,433 --> 00:09:50,100
What?

177
00:09:51,267 --> 00:09:52,933
Bok, let's go!

178
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:05,733
- Sis!
- Oh?

179
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:06,933
Watch this.

180
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:09,533
- Hurry up.
- What's that?

181
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:13,000
<i>My fellow netizens,
breaking news.</i>

182
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:14,900
<i>There's an ongoing
hostage situation</i>

183
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:16,700
<i> right here at Station 12.</i>

184
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:18,133
Hostage taking?

185
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:19,733
At Station 12?

186
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:21,033
- Wait, wait.
- Oh...

187
00:10:21,167 --> 00:10:24,500
Wait, isn't Sir Tonyo
assigned to Station 12?

188
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,433
Wait...

189
00:10:31,033 --> 00:10:32,533
Answer the phone.

190
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,733
Wait, what's wrong with you?
Why don't you answer?

191
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:43,533
What? Sir Tonyo isn't answering.

192
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:46,167
No, it's not Sir Tonyo
I'm calling.

193
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:47,733
What? Who?

194
00:10:47,867 --> 00:10:48,733
It's Sir Eric.

195
00:10:50,167 --> 00:10:51,100
Sir Eric?

196
00:10:52,067 --> 00:10:54,767
Answer the phone.
What's wrong?

197
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:57,633
Eric!

198
00:10:57,767 --> 00:10:58,600
Why Sir Eric?

199
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,667
<i>A police officer has taken his
colleague hostage</i>

200
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,133
<i> for unknown reasons.</i>

201
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:08,700
<i>- Stay tuned for more updates.
- Oh my God.</i>

202
00:11:11,467 --> 00:11:12,400
Hello, Glen?

203
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:14,133
Have you seen the news?

204
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:16,133
Yes, just now.

205
00:11:16,267 --> 00:11:17,833
<i> What's your plan?</i>

206
00:11:17,967 --> 00:11:20,533
Oh, let the police handle
the situation?

207
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:21,667
Wrong.

208
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:25,067
I thought you wanted Calabari
to love you?

209
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,500
What do you suggest I do?

210
00:11:26,633 --> 00:11:28,167
I rushed over there.

211
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:29,867
I'll try to be a hero?

212
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,967
I'll shoot the hostage takers?

213
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:35,067
Well, that will make you
a dead man,

214
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:38,533
And you're not an action star
like your father.

215
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:41,367
So what do you suggest I do,
Mom?

216
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:44,933
Take a page out of your
Godfather Victor's playbook.

217
00:11:45,067 --> 00:11:48,100
You make the hostage taker
surrender.

218
00:11:48,233 --> 00:11:51,667
That would make you
Calabari's new hero.

219
00:11:57,367 --> 00:11:59,367
That's a great idea, Mom.

220
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:02,333
I'm going to Station 12
right now.

221
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:04,333
Very good, Son.

222
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:23,200
Are you going to resign
from the police force?

223
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,767
But don't you love your job?

224
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:29,800
I know, that was your dream
since you were a kid, right?

225
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:32,167
Well, my dreams have come true.

226
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:34,500
I've become a police officer
already, right?

227
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:37,367
But you're not a detective yet,

228
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,800
which is your end goal.

229
00:12:39,933 --> 00:12:41,467
- Right?
- Yes.

230
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:45,500
Well...

231
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:46,867
I don't want to rely on you

232
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,667
the responsibilities of my
grandmother.

233
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,733
That is not right, right?

234
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:54,067
But you know, Bobby,

235
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:58,033
Mar and I are not complaining.

236
00:12:58,567 --> 00:13:02,767
Yes, and captain is our family,
what's with you?

237
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:07,900
Yes, but I don't want it to get
to the point where I'm working,

238
00:13:08,033 --> 00:13:11,100
and then my mind is here,
with grandmother.

239
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:14,033
But you know, Bobby, with the
way you're speaking,

240
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:16,133
It sounds like
you're about to resign too.

241
00:13:16,267 --> 00:13:17,200
So what now?

242
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:21,833
You're going to say
goodbye to Tonyo?

243
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,767
Why would I say goodbye to him
when we're not together?

244
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:27,167
- You're not together?
- Really?

245
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,600
But he was the first person
you called

246
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:30,700
when you found out about
captain's illness.

247
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:33,200
That's because Chief wasn't
answering!

248
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:36,567
That's why I called Tonyo and
asked permission from him.

249
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:39,267
Oh my, with so many people
you can call, why Tonyo?

250
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,867
That's right.

251
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:55,833
Hey! Hey!

252
00:13:56,867 --> 00:13:58,000
Not there.

253
00:13:58,133 --> 00:13:59,600
There.

254
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:10,067
Bautista, handcuff Dizon.

255
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,600
I don't want to.

256
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:13,833
Hurry up!

257
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:19,667
Sir...

258
00:14:22,133 --> 00:14:23,533
handcuff him there.

259
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,800
Sir, sorry, Sir.

260
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:44,800
<i> Is Bobby at Station 12?</i>

261
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:46,333
<i>A police officer running amok at
Station 12.</i>

262
00:14:46,467 --> 00:14:47,500
Oh my!

263
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:49,100
This is crazy!

264
00:14:49,233 --> 00:14:51,233
- Why?
- What's wrong with you?

265
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:55,467
My friend is asking if you in
the Station 12?

266
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:56,667
Oh.

267
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,200
He said a police officer
went amok.

268
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:02,333
He hostage his colleagues at
Station 12.

269
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,100
What?

270
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,400
Sir, the major has lost
a lot of blood.

271
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:15,767
We need to get him
to the hospital.

272
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:17,200
Stop it!

273
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:19,000
If anyone leaves here,

274
00:15:19,133 --> 00:15:21,633
it's me, not the chief.

275
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:22,667
Do you understand?

276
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:26,633
Robles, how are you
going to get out?

277
00:15:26,767 --> 00:15:28,633
If you don't want to get hurt,

278
00:15:28,767 --> 00:15:29,767
surrender.

279
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,533
What am I, crazy?

280
00:15:32,667 --> 00:15:35,933
If I do that,
you'll all kill me!

281
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:39,300
What are you talking about?

282
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:41,367
Why would we do that?

283
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,200
What's wrong with you?

284
00:15:44,733 --> 00:15:45,567
Robles...

285
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:48,167
surrender now.

286
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:53,433
I'll make you a state witness,

287
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:57,800
but you have to expose
the syndicates.

288
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:18,567
Robles, stop this already.

289
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,200
You should surrender.

290
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:23,233
Sir, Major is getting weak.

291
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:25,800
Let us take him to the hospital.

292
00:16:30,267 --> 00:16:31,733
Sir, what's with you?

293
00:16:31,867 --> 00:16:33,933
You're so noisy! You've been
like that for a while now!

294
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:39,800
Robles!

295
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:40,767
What's with you?

296
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:42,633
Stop that!

297
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:45,633
You, did I tell you to talk?

298
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:47,133
Try to open your mouth
one more time,

299
00:16:47,267 --> 00:16:48,367
and I'll blow your skull off!

300
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,267
Go! Go!

301
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:53,533
What? Huh?

302
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:55,200
You're not going to stop?

303
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:59,000
- Noble!
- Yes, Ma'am?

304
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:00,300
Do you have Robles' number?

305
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:01,967
- Yes.
- Call him.

306
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:15,033
Hello?

307
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,500
Robles, this is
Lieutenant Samson

308
00:17:18,633 --> 00:17:20,067
Oh...

309
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,167
<i> Lieutenant Samson...</i>

310
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:24,500
<i> How are you?</i>

311
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:28,300
You know, I've been wanting to
ask you for a long time

312
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:30,300
if you're single.

313
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:32,067
Do you want to go on
a date with me?

314
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,233
Are you game?

315
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:35,233
What was that gunshot we heard?

316
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:37,033
Oh...

317
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:38,500
That's nothing.

318
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:41,700
It's Bautista, she's wounded.

319
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:43,700
She's so noisy,
and I'm getting pissed.

320
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:46,067
What? You shot Bautista?

321
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,033
Relax, relax.

322
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,633
She's still alive,

323
00:17:49,767 --> 00:17:51,267
for now.

324
00:17:53,033 --> 00:17:55,733
But if you won't give me
what I want...

325
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:59,333
I might kill her...

326
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:01,533
or Chief,

327
00:18:01,667 --> 00:18:02,933
or Dizon.

328
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,700
What do you want?

329
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:10,267
It's simple.

330
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,800
Give me a helicopter

331
00:18:11,933 --> 00:18:14,233
so I can escape
from here safely.

332
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:15,633
That's all?

333
00:18:15,767 --> 00:18:17,367
If you want, come with me.

334
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:18,900
No problem either.

335
00:18:19,033 --> 00:18:21,900
Okay, I'll see if I can
handle your request, okay?

336
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:24,000
Do it!

337
00:18:24,133 --> 00:18:25,967
Because if
you can't handle it...

338
00:18:27,267 --> 00:18:29,933
I'll kill one of my companions
here right now.

339
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,900
Do you understand?

340
00:18:59,033 --> 00:19:00,300
Excuse, excuse.

341
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:02,167
Move, move, move.

342
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:03,400
Ma'am, I already called.

343
00:19:03,533 --> 00:19:04,500
The SWAT is on its way.

344
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:07,133
Samson!

345
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:09,067
What's the status inside?

346
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:12,633
It's Robles, he took Dizon,
chief, and Bautista hostage.

347
00:19:12,767 --> 00:19:15,133
Bautista and chief
were also shot.

348
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:16,500
How are they doing?

349
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:18,333
According to Robles,
they are still alive.

350
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:21,033
But, Sir, Chief's shot
is dangerous.

351
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:22,767
What's going on with Robles,
Tonyo?

352
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,333
Why is he acting like this?

353
00:19:24,467 --> 00:19:26,767
That can only mean one thing.

354
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:27,767
He already found out

355
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:31,267
that we know he's part of the
syndicate.

356
00:19:31,433 --> 00:19:33,633
My suspicion is correct, Bok.

357
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:35,400
Someone is watching us.

358
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:39,467
What does Robles need?

359
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:40,633
A helicopter.

360
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:41,700
He gave a deadline.

361
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:43,200
If the helicopter isn't here
in thirty minutes,

362
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:45,200
he'll kill one of his hostages.

363
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:46,933
But, Sir, I've already
called SWAT.

364
00:19:47,067 --> 00:19:47,933
They're on their way.

365
00:19:49,667 --> 00:19:53,367
So we need to console Robles
while SWAT isn't here.

366
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,000
Are you going up?

367
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:57,200
We can't just stand there
and watch.

368
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:00,100
He'll just kill
our comrades up there.

369
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:04,233
Bok, what if we just tell him

370
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:07,200
that the helicopter
is on its way?

371
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:09,333
He won't believe us.

372
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,200
Let's do this.

373
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:15,933
Lieutenant Samson,
when I call you later,

374
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:18,833
you radio him and tell him that
the helicopter is on its way.

375
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:20,400
Okay.

376
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:23,300
Let's go, Bok!

377
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,400
Hello?

378
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:41,100
What do you need?

379
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:42,800
Robles...

380
00:20:42,933 --> 00:20:45,267
I heard you've added
more victims.

381
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:48,767
Maybe you want me to follow next
when I get out of here.

382
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:50,000
Relax, Robles.

383
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:51,733
You're too serious.

384
00:20:52,233 --> 00:20:54,667
You know, if you don't have
anything sensible to say,

385
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,067
can we just end this call?

386
00:20:57,200 --> 00:21:01,167
I called you because the mayor
has something to say.

387
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:04,000
What's that?

388
00:21:04,133 --> 00:21:06,000
He said you should surrender.

389
00:21:06,133 --> 00:21:08,233
Are you kidding?

390
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,100
I shot two police officers here.

391
00:21:10,233 --> 00:21:12,767
You want me to surrender, huh?

392
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:14,367
You know, you're too excited.

393
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:15,500
You're not listening.

394
00:21:15,633 --> 00:21:17,000
Wait a minute.

395
00:21:17,133 --> 00:21:20,167
The Mayor's order is to
surrender,

396
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:22,433
but not to the cops.

397
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:24,933
You'll surrender to him.

398
00:21:25,067 --> 00:21:27,067
He said he'll take care of you.

399
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,433
Okay, okay.

400
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:30,567
I'll wait for the boss' call.

401
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:34,700
Just tell him nothing bad should
happen to me.

402
00:21:58,167 --> 00:21:59,367
What now?

403
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,900
The time I've been waiting
for is over.

404
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:07,267
So that means I can kill now.

405
00:22:09,067 --> 00:22:10,700
Do you want to go first,

406
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:13,300
you talkative little brat!

407
00:22:13,433 --> 00:22:15,167
No.

408
00:22:15,333 --> 00:22:17,467
Or maybe you want to go first,
Major?

409
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:22,033
Or maybe you, Bok?

410
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:26,333
Let's do this...

411
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:28,433
Eenie...

412
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:30,933
Meenie...

413
00:22:31,067 --> 00:22:31,967
Miney...

414
00:22:34,033 --> 00:22:35,633
Mo.

415
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:56,700
Who are those police officers
who broke in?

416
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:57,900
Is it Tonyo?

417
00:22:58,033 --> 00:23:00,800
Because I can't see Tonyo and
Sir Eric outside.

418
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:02,733
I hope they're safe!

419
00:23:02,867 --> 00:23:06,700
I promise I'll do anything to
reduce your sentence.

420
00:23:06,833 --> 00:23:10,167
Let me remind you that we don't
want to arrest you,

421
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:13,033
but whoever the head
of the syndicate is.

422
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:14,700
Let me talk
to the hostage taker.

423
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:16,233
What you want to do
is dangerous.

424
00:23:16,367 --> 00:23:17,500
Let's just wait for an update.

425
00:23:17,633 --> 00:23:18,933
Get out of there,

426
00:23:19,067 --> 00:23:21,867
and when I escape, save Chief.

427
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:25,400
But promise me you won't hurt
our colleagues inside.

428
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:27,100
That's a promise.
